  "response_text": "A kitchen counter is crowded with dirty dishes against a glossy blue subway-tile backsplash. Two small ducklings, yellow with darker brown backs and head stripes, stand in the narrow open space between stacks of plates and bowls smeared with food residue. On the right, an adult hand with a wedding band pushes a tall stack of dirty plates closer to them, making the ducklings look boxed in by the dishes. The ducklings face each other and the moving stack, their beaks slightly open as if reacting. From above, the counter looks even more cluttered: a large white plate with brown greasy smears fills the foreground, bowls and plastic containers sit nearby, and kitchen tools such as a grater and whisk are visible to the side. The ducklings stand below the plate, looking upward amid the mess.\n\nThe view shifts to the ducklings at counter level, now close to the viewer, with the kitchen sink area behind them. In the background, slightly out of focus, two adults stand at the sink washing dishes; one appears to be holding a plate while another’s soapy hands work near the basin. Between the ducklings and the people, a blue bottle of Dawn Platinum Plus PowerSuds sits upright on the counter. As the ducklings move aside, the bottle becomes centered and prominent. It is a tall, clear plastic squeeze bottle filled with deep blue liquid, with a large label reading “DAWN Platinum Plus PowerSuds.” Smaller label text indicates it removes grease and has “trap & lock suds,” with “Fresh Rain” near the bottom. Around it are a pale green bowl, a faucet, suds at the sink, and stacks of dirty plates, emphasizing the dishwashing setting.\n\nA product demonstration follows. A hand presses a blue sponge covered in thick white suds across a white plate coated with brown, greasy residue. On the right side of the screen, a solid blue panel displays large block text in light blue: “TRAP,” “LOCK,” and “REMOVE,” stacked vertically, with smaller words “UP TO” beside “REMOVE.” As the sponge slides across the plate, it leaves a clean white path through the grease, pushing foamy suds ahead of it while brown residue remains only along the edges. The plate is then shown closer, tilted slightly, with a mass of suds trapping yellowish grease. The on-screen text completes to read “TRAP LOCK REMOVE UP TO 99% OF GREASE,” with “99%” in large yellow numbers and “OF GREASE” below it.\n\nThe cleaning comparison is shown in a side-by-side layout divided by a vertical blue line. On the left, labeled “ORDINARY DISH SOAP,” a hand scrubs a greasy metal pan with a blue sponge; the suds appear thin and spread across visible streaks of residue. On the right, labeled “DAWN POWERSUDS,” another hand scrubs a similar pan with more dense white foam, and the surface looks clearer as the sponge moves. The comparison continues with transparent plastic containers. On the left, under “ORDINARY DISH SOAP,” the container still looks cloudy or filmed after scrubbing. On the right, under “DAWN POWERSUDS,” the container is filled with thicker suds during scrubbing, and when lifted or shown afterward, it appears clearer and cleaner than the one on the left.\n\nBack at the kitchen counter, the dishes are now clean and neatly arranged upright in a metal drying rack beside the sink. Plates line up in a tidy row, with a translucent plastic container propped among them. The two ducklings stand in front of the rack on the shiny counter, no longer trapped. One faces the other with its beak open, while the other stands beside it, both looking relaxed and animated. A blue Dawn bottle remains visible in the background near the sink.\n\nThe commercial ends on a bright blue product display. Large text on the left reads “THE BETTER GREASE GETTER,” with “THE” and “BETTER” in light blue and “GREASE GETTER” in yellow. In the center stands the Dawn Platinum Plus PowerSuds bottle with a small “NEW” badge near the top. Two ducklings stand to the right of the bottle on or beside a blue sponge, one leaning toward the product. A small P&G logo appears in the upper-right corner.",
